column5: Good job Simon. In Southern Ontario, unless you're 7.5' tall, an auger extension is pretty useless.  You're all set for next year too!
One day, there will be a "Limeyangler" signature series ice rod that has the bells pre-attached    Nice haul there sir!
Must have been a decent sale on that Garmin. It's got me thinking.,..  but then again I have nearly 100 things on my list already it seems.
And if you live where I do 2 extensions are necessary!!!
CTC flyer says 50% off on select Garmin GPS models.
Hurry! I can hear you wife coming. Hide that stuff in with your other tackle and eat the receipts.
LOL!! Eat the receipts! Where'd ya ever get that idea from???
great score, especially the Garmin. you'll love that rod.
Good to see you got the Garmin.. Around here all the CTC sold out really fast.. Out of stock before closing Friday
